 {"id":"flywheel_gateway-4hh","title":"Implement GitHub checksummed releases with auto-update","description":"## Task
Implement checksummed GitHub releases with SHA256 verification and automatic update checking for Flywheel Gateway binaries/packages.

## Why This Matters
- Per user request: "easy to update automatically using github and checksummed releases"
- Per GitHub research (June 2025): "GitHub Releases now exposes SHA256 digests for newly published release assets"
- Security: Prevents supply chain attacks via tampered binaries
- Reliability: Ensures downloaded files are exactly what was published
- Automation: Enables safe unattended updates

## Files to Create/Modify
1. .github/workflows/release.yml (checksums generation)
2. scripts/generate-checksums.ts (checksum generation script)
3. scripts/verify-download.ts (verification script)
4. apps/gateway/src/services/update-checker.service.ts (NEW)
5. packages/shared/src/update-types.ts (types)

## Release Workflow with Checksums
```yaml
# .github/workflows/release.yml
name: Release

on:
  push:
    tags:
      - 'v*'

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Setup Bun
        uses: oven-sh/setup-bun@v1
        with:
          bun-version: latest

      - name: Build
        run: bun run build

      - name: Create release artifacts
        run: |
          # Create tarballs for each platform
          tar -czvf flywheel-gateway-linux-x64.tar.gz -C dist .
          tar -czvf flywheel-gateway-darwin-x64.tar.gz -C dist .
          tar -czvf flywheel-gateway-darwin-arm64.tar.gz -C dist .

      - name: Generate checksums
        run: |
          # Generate SHA256 checksums
          sha256sum flywheel-gateway-*.tar.gz > checksums.txt

          # Also generate individual .sha256 files
          for file in flywheel-gateway-*.tar.gz; do
            sha256sum "$file" > "${file}.sha256"
          done

          # Sign checksums file with GPG (optional but recommended)
          # gpg --armor --detach-sign checksums.txt

      - name: Create GitHub Release
        uses: softprops/action-gh-release@v1
        with:
          files: |
            flywheel-gateway-*.tar.gz
            flywheel-gateway-*.tar.gz.sha256
            checksums.txt
          generate_release_notes: true
          body: |
            ## Checksums

            Verify your download:
            \`\`\`bash
            sha256sum -c checksums.txt
            \`\`\`

            Or individually:
            \`\`\`bash
            sha256sum -c flywheel-gateway-linux-x64.tar.gz.sha256
            \`\`\`
